Creating a user
Ex:
root@ip-172-31-40-238:/home/ubuntu/devops-lab# sudo adduser ram
New password: 
Retype new password: 
passwd: password updated successfully
Changing the user information for ram
Enter the new value, or press ENTER for the default
        Full Name []: ram
        Room Number []: 1
        Work Phone []: 1'
        Home Phone []: 2
        Other []: 2
Is the information correct? [Y/n] y

To check if users are created : cat /etc/passwd 
if we create any user, the user will be added to /etc/passwd file, so we can see there

Creating a group:
Ex: sudo groupadd g1

Adding user to group:
Ex: sudo useradd -aG g1 ram
# -a: for append, G: for adding user to group (mandatory)
Verify: groups ram

Grant admin access to that user:
sudo usermod -aG sudo ram

Switch to that user:
su - ram




